	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>With a few exceptions, the majority of people here seem to suggest the strongest races make the best warriors.&nbsp;&nbsp;I disagree.  There's more to being a warrior than just muscle power.  ALL of the physical stats are important.  Str for hitting and wearing heavy armor, sta for lasting in a fight, dex for hitting for critical more often, agi for ac dodging and blocking.  I would have to agree with Nowalls.  Halflings make an excellent warrior for beginners.  Good stats, small armor is cheaper,excellent newbie zone, infravision, centrally located home city, great newbie quests, not to mention hide and sneak when trouble arises.  A 3 foot guy in armor with a little sword is not too intimidating, I realize.  But I have always, and will always, place function over form.<br><br>Ganthan Battlemoore<br>32nd warrior<br>Bertoxxulous server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
