	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=8016><span id= >Galoote</span></a><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The big races are better because they can slam without a shield. I doubt the iksar AC bonus is that great. Regeneration counts for nothing too.<br>Big races can dual wield and still slam to interupt casters and when you are fighting numerous mobs that heal themselves this is a must have. As for which is better between trolls and ogres i would pick trolls. People seem to think ogres are better becasue of their strenght but in practice strength makes little difference to actual damage caused. The biggest factors are your level bonus and the weapons you are using along with whether or not you are dual wielding. Race make no difference to these. Therefore I reckon the best race for a warrior is a troll. Trolls get a slight agility bonus giving them a slightly better AC, they also have a decent strenght for carrying armour, they have a decent stamina for hit point bonuses, they can slam with no shield, and they are not quite as fat as Ogres allowing them to squeeze past more obstacles. I suppose at low levels their regeneration is pretty useful too. The only big disadvantage to being a troll is faction but to be frank who cares are there is still plenty of stuff to kill and the human towns are boring and all look alike anyways. <br>Well theres my thesis on the matter I hope this helps someone.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
